# CODEOWNERS — the verification trusted computing base (TCB)
#
# WHY THIS EXISTS
# Máddu's north star is "don't let the actor be the sole witness." An agent that
# can silently rewrite its own oracle — the artifacts that decide pass/fail — IS
# the sole witness. Every control inside Máddu runs inside the agent's process:
# `discipline.mjs` is fail-open by law, every gate is code the agent can edit,
# every baseline is a file the agent can rewrite. This file is the ONE control an
# in-repo agent cannot reach, because GitHub enforces it, not Máddu.
#
# STATUS: INERT UNTIL BRANCH PROTECTION IS ENABLED.
# CODEOWNERS has no effect on its own. It takes effect only once `main` requires
# code-owner review. Until then this file documents the intended boundary and
# nothing more. Do not describe it as protection in README, site copy, or release
# notes while it is inert. See docs/46-ci.md.
#
# SCOPE — two layers, and the second is the one that is easy to miss.
# Protecting only tests and gate definitions is NOT enough: .github/workflows/
# maddu-ci.yml checks out PR-controlled code and runs `node bin/maddu.mjs ci`, so
# an agent can rewrite the VERDICT LOGIC (verify.mjs, gates.mjs, the runners)
# without touching a single test file. Both layers must be owned together or
# neither is meaningful.
#
# ACCEPTED RESIDUAL: CI still executes PR-controlled code. Fully closing that
# needs the required check to run from the protected base branch or an immutable
# action. Documented in docs/34-threat-model.md — NOT claimed as solved.
#
# Syntax note: LAST matching pattern wins, so the catch-all is first and the
# self-protecting entry is last.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default — no global owner. Ordinary feature work stays frictionless; only the
# paths named below require independent approval.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Layer 1 — THE ORACLE: artifacts that decide pass/fail.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/scripts/test/                                        @frdyx
/template/maddu/runtime/gates/                        @frdyx
/.maddu/config/ci.json                                @frdyx
/.github/                                             @frdyx

# Forward declaration — arrives with the tracked-source pin.
# PRECONDITION: .maddu/config/* is gitignored (.gitignore:15), so this entry is
# DEAD until the file is un-ignored the way ci.json already is (.gitignore:20).
# A gitignored file never appears in a PR diff, so CODEOWNERS can never fire on
# it. Un-ignoring it is a hard requirement of that work, not a tidy-up.
/.maddu/config/tracked-sources.json                   @frdyx

# NOT LISTED, DELIBERATELY: /.maddu/gates/
# Operator gates shadow builtins by id (gates.mjs:51,57-59), so the directory is
# a real attack surface — but .maddu/* is gitignored (.gitignore:11), so such a
# gate never reaches a PR diff or a CI checkout. CODEOWNERS cannot reach it and
# listing it here would be decoration. Consequence: gate shadowing is a
# LOCAL-ONLY threat (it poisons `maddu ci` / `doctor` on the developer's machine,
# never the required GitHub check). Covered instead by the `unpinned` drift class
# in the tracked-source work. Documented in docs/34-threat-model.md.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Layer 2 — THE VERIFIER: code that produces or interprets the verdict.
# Editing any of these changes what "green" means without touching a test.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/bin/maddu.mjs                                        @frdyx
/commands/ci.mjs                                      @frdyx
/commands/sources.mjs                                 @frdyx
/commands/_project-test-runner.mjs                    @frdyx
/template/maddu/runtime/lib/gates.mjs                 @frdyx
/template/maddu/runtime/lib/verify.mjs                @frdyx
/template/maddu/runtime/lib/spine.mjs                 @frdyx
/template/maddu/runtime/lib/projections.mjs           @frdyx
/template/maddu/runtime/lib/verification-recency.mjs  @frdyx
/template/maddu/runtime/lib/event-schema.mjs          @frdyx
/template/maddu/runtime/lib/event-dispositions.mjs    @frdyx

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The boundary protects itself — otherwise the first move against it is to
# quietly narrow this list.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/.github/CODEOWNERS                                   @frdyx
